   <body>
      <context>You must authorize your Zoom account to <ph href="../../../../Warehouse/Product_Name_Warehouse.xml#reference-9043/product_name"/>for the first time and anytime in future, when authorization is invalid in <ph href="../../../../Warehouse/Product_Name_Warehouse.xml#reference-9043/product_name"/>.<p>Perform the following steps to install and authorize the Zoom App.</p>
      </context>
      <ol>
         <li>
            <p>In the module menu, click<uicontrol>Projects</uicontrol>.</p>
            <p>The<uicontrol>PROJECTS</uicontrol>list page is displayed.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>In the<uicontrol>PROJECTS</uicontrol>list page, click the required project, and then click<uicontrol>Edit</uicontrol>.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>In the navigation pane, expand the project folder.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Expand<uicontrol>Collaboration</uicontrol>, and then click<uicontrol>Meeting Scheduler</uicontrol>.</p>
            <p>The<uicontrol>MEETING SCHEDULER</uicontrol>list page is displayed.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Click<uicontrol>Authorize</uicontrol>.</p>
            <p>The<uicontrol>ZOOM SIGN IN</uicontrol>page opens in a different tab.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Login to your Zoom account and authorize Mind to access your Zoom account.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Navigate to the <ph href="../../../../Warehouse/Product_Name_Warehouse.xml#reference-9043/product_name"/> tab.</p>
         </li>
      </ol>
